# Domains that block automated clients (return 403/503 to anything that is
# not a real browser), so checking them from CI produces false positives.
# They still need an occasional manual check.
https://www\.amazon\.com/.*
https://book\.douban\.com/.*
https://www\.reddit\.com/.*
https://www\.levels\.fyi/.*
# Ozon's anti-bot answers with an endless 307 redirect loop (?__rr=N).
https://www\.ozon\.ru/.*
# Epic Games and Medium return 403 to non-browser clients.
https://www\.unrealengine\.com/.*
https://medium\.com/.*
# cppreference and isocpp are fine from browsers and residential IPs, but
# their CDN returns 403 to GitHub-hosted runner (datacenter) IPs.
https://(en|ru|zh)\.cppreference\.com/.*
https://isocpp\.org/.*
# Intel blocks automated clients (bots)
https://www\.intel\.com/.*
